	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=item.html?item=6140&mid=100210462753266>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=item.html?item=6140&mid=100210462753266>RE: I have some for sale</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=6140&mid=100210462753266#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Oct 3rd 6:23 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=84649><span id=Scholar>Troodon</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>704 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.76]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Note that these aren't the only cheap 10 slot containers you can buy anymore.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you go to the gnome pirate outpost in Iceclad Ocean, you can buy deluxe toolboxes for about 1 1/2pp each.  They are 10 slot containers, weigh 3.5, no weight reduction, and can hold giant or smaller items.  Obviously this is a crappy container for lugging things around in, unless you really had no other container with a giant capacity, but they're excellent to keep in the bank for storing items.  These items can also be used with gnomes' tinkering skill.<br><br>No point in paying the rediculous prices deluxe sewing kits go for anymore.  They now only exist in the hands of players who owned a large sewing kit before the patch changed them to deluxe sewing kits.  Merchants don't sell them anymore, and any that were sold to merchants were instantly destroyed.  If you want to make a tailored item with more than 8 ingredients, you have to find a community loom if you don't happen to have a deluxe sewing kit.</p>&nbsp;<br>Troodon, AKA Zararazu Twoflower, Level 61 Iksar Monk, Jaggedpine Defender, Solusek Ro<br><br>My profile: <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=91426" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=91426</a></td></td></tr>
