	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f99987353119623>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=item.html?item=6140&mid=99987353119623>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=item.html?item=6140&mid=99987353119623>a bit of history</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=6140&mid=99987353119623#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Sep 7th 10:38 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=651><span id=Sage>Verdandi</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>59 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Way back at the dawn of time, two kinds of tailoring kits were available from vendors: large (8 slots) and small (2 slots).&nbsp;&nbsp;Then, when cultural tailoring (for halflings, erudites, and wood elves) was added, new kits (10 slots) were introduced that could only be used by those two races to make their cultural armors.  When Velious came out, another kit was made available from stores in Velious cities, the coldain tanning kit (8 slots) that must be used to make the Velious tailored armors.  <br><br>Then, because they were about to introduce old world armor that had more than 8 ingredients, the old world original large kits were increased to have 10 slots.  But then, people started complaining more loudly because this change meant that the large tailoring kits had as many slots as tailored backpacks but weighed less and held bigger items.  So, the Powers That Be decided to remove the 10 slot tailoring kits from vendors.  The problem was that they couldn't simply change them back to 8 slots, because that would cause problems for people who had items in all 10 slots.  So, they changed the existing 10-slot large kits into a new item, Deluxe kits, and changed vendors back to the original large kits with only 8 slots.  <br><br>Therefore, the only deluxe tailoring kits in existance are ones that players had in their possession when these changes were made.  If you find them on a vendor, it is because someone sold it to that vendor.  For those who need 10 slots for the recipes with more than 8 ingredients (Wu's Fighting armor), they also added Looms to some cities.  Looms are stationary containers that you go to in a city and use on the spot, like ovens or brew barrels or forges. <br><br>(Credit goes to Oakwood Moonblaze and Schmoozo Gladhand for their post here:) <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/feqtraderscornertailoring.showMessage?topicID=2666.topic" target=_new>http://pub13.ezboard.com/feqtraderscornertailoring.showMessage?topicID=2666.topic</a></p>&nbsp;<br>Venerable Heyokah Verdandi Snowblood, Hierophant of Cabilis, Barbarian Prophet, and Fluffy Pillow for the Celestial Knights</td></td></tr>
